    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-07-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-07-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="143"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d143">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Beaupré</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-07-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 13, 1903</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Neither of the proposed amendments mentioned in your telegram<note n="a"
                        xml:id="d143fna">Dated July 9.</note> received to-day would stand any chance
                    of acceptance by the Senate of the United States, while any amendment whatever
                    or unnecessary delay in the ratification of the treaty would greatly imperil its
                    consummation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
